# Ndila Connect Services Website - Development Standards

## Project Overview
Personal and business website for Ndila Connect Services built with Next.js, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS.
- Template: Lume Studio Next (haramishra/lume-studio-next)
- License: MIT
- Hosting: Vercel / Azure / Custom (TBD)

## Development Standards

### Git Strategy
- **Main branches**: `main` (production), `dev` (staging)
- **Feature branches**: `feature/feature-name`, `fix/bug-name`, `chore/task-name`
- **Commit format**: Conventional commits
  - `feat: add new feature`
  - `fix: resolve bug`
  - `docs: update documentation`
  - `style: format code`
  - `chore: maintenance tasks`

### Code Standards
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Framework**: Next.js 15+
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4
- **Component Library**: Radix UI, Lucide Icons
- **Code style**: ESLint configuration included
- **No AI-generated visuals**: Use professional, clean icons only

### File Organization
```
src/
├── app/           # Next.js app router pages
├── components/    # Reusable React components
├── content/       # Static content (markdown, data)
├── hooks/         # Custom React hooks
├── lib/           # Utility functions and helpers
├── styles/        # Global styles (if needed beyond Tailwind)
└── types/         # TypeScript type definitions
```

### Component Standards
- Use TypeScript interfaces for props
- Functional components only
- Client-side rendering with `'use client'` when needed
- Server components as default

### Error Handling
- Structured logging with context (timestamp, level, message, error details)
- Try-catch blocks with proper error propagation
- User-friendly error messages in UI
- Detailed logs for debugging

### Testing
- Unit tests for utilities and hooks
- Integration tests for API routes
- End-to-end tests for critical flows
- Test files: `*.test.ts` or `*.spec.ts`

### Security
- Input validation on frontend AND backend
- SMTP credentials via environment variables
- Secure file upload handling (size limits, type validation)
- CSRF protection
- Rate limiting on API endpoints

### SEO & Metadata
- Meta tags on all pages
- Open Graph tags for social sharing
- Structured data (JSON-LD)
- Sitemap.xml and robots.txt
- Mobile responsive design first

### Environment Variables
```
.env.local (local development)
.env.example (template for CI/CD)

Required variables:
- NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL
- SMTP_HOST
- SMTP_PORT
- SMTP_USER
- SMTP_PASS
- CONTACT_EMAIL
- NEXT_PUBLIC_ANALYTICS_ID (optional)
```

### CI/CD Pipeline (GitHub Actions)
- On PR: Run linting, type check, build test
- On merge to main: Build, test, deploy to production
- On merge to dev: Deploy to staging

### Performance
- Image optimization (Next.js Image component)
- Code splitting enabled by default
- Minimal animations (fade-in, slide-in only)
- No external tracking scripts unless justified

## Pages & Routes
- `/` - Home
- `/about` - About company and founder
- `/services` - Service offerings
- `/portfolio` - Case studies and projects
- `/tenders` - Tenders and compliance documentation
